    <bioghist encodinganalog="5451_">
      <p> Basin, Montana, was established in 1880 as a gold mining town on the site of the former
        town of Cataract. The post office was established in 1880 and has operated continuously ever
        since.</p>
    </bioghist>
    <scopecontent encodinganalog="5202_">
      <p> Records (1899-1931) include cash books (1902-1917); postmaster's account and record books
        (1900-1917); registers (1899-1916, 1923-1931) of money orders issued and received; register
        (1905-1919) of notices to publishers of removed and unknown addressees; registered mail
        receipts (1908-1922); and stamp impression books (1905-1910, 1917). </p>
    </scopecontent>
